quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  11,46,"Allah said, “O Noah, he is not of your family, for he was not righteous in his conduct. So do not ask Me of what you have no knowledge. I admonish you, so you do not be among the ignorant.”",""
  11,47,"Noah said, “My Lord, I seek refuge with You from asking You that of which I have no knowledge. Unless You forgive me and have mercy upon me, I will be among the losers.”",""
  11,48,"It was said, “O Noah, disembark with peace from Us, and with blessings upon you and upon some nations [descending] from those who are with you. As for other nations, We will grant them enjoyment for a while, then they will be afflicted with a painful punishment from Us.”",""
  11,49,"This is one of the stories of the unseen that we reveal to you [O Prophet]; neither you nor your people knew it before this. So be patient; the outcome is for the righteous.",""
  11,50,"To the people of ‘Ād<sup>24</sup> We sent their brother Hūd. He said, “O my people, worship Allah; you have no god other than Him. You are but fabricators<sup>25</sup>.","[24] An Arabian tribe who rebelled against their Messenger, so Allah destroyed them.\n [25] Their claim to worship others besides Allah was a groundless lie."
  11,51,"O my people, I ask you no reward for it. My reward is only with the One Who created me. Do you not then understand?",""
  11,52,"O my people, seek forgiveness of your Lord and turn to Him in repentance; He will send down upon you abundant rain from the sky and will add strength to your strength. So do not turn away in wickedness.”",""
  11,53,"They said, “O Hūd, you have not brought us any clear evidence, and we will not forsake our gods on account of what you say, nor will we believe in you.",""
